en_775204_0	Kilinochchi-based troops at the request of church authorities offered their help to launch a Shramadana campaign to rid waste paper, garbage and environmental pollutants from the Amathiyapuram Vellankanni Roman Catholic Church premises on Thursday (28).
en_775204_1	7 Sri Lanka National Guard (SLNG) troops of the 652 Brigade under the 65 Division of the Security Force Headquarters - Kilinochchi contributed to this project and cleaned the premises with the participation of more than 32 Army personnel.
en_775204_2	Major General Vijitha Ravipriya, Commander, Security Forces - Kilinochchi has given his blessings to the project under the supervision of Major General Wasantha Kumarapperuma, General Officer Commanding, 65 Division.
